<main><div class="animated-bg-container" data-astro-cid-do4sevwe><div class="grid-overlay" data-astro-cid-do4sevwe></div><div class="gradient-orb orb-1" data-astro-cid-do4sevwe></div><div class="gradient-orb orb-2" data-astro-cid-do4sevwe></div><div class="gradient-orb orb-3" data-astro-cid-do4sevwe></div><div class="particles" data-astro-cid-do4sevwe></div></div><div class="floating-elements" data-astro-cid-fgearzst><div class="float-shape shape-1" data-astro-cid-fgearzst></div><div class="float-shape shape-2" data-astro-cid-fgearzst></div><div class="float-shape shape-3" data-astro-cid-fgearzst></div><div class="float-shape shape-4" data-astro-cid-fgearzst></div><div class="float-shape shape-5" data-astro-cid-fgearzst></div></div><div class="shapes-3d-container" data-astro-cid-ef6knh6u><canvas data-astro-cid-ef6knh6u id="shapes-canvas"></canvas><div class="spark-container" data-astro-cid-ef6knh6u></div></div><section class="mx-auto relative px-4 max-w-4xl z-10 pb-10 pt-24 sm:pt-28"><span class="text-sm glitch-text text-primary tracking-[0.6em] uppercase" data-astro-cid-5jggg6be data-text="Mission brief">Mission brief</span><header class="border bg-white border-gray-200 px-6 py-10 rounded-[32px] shadow-xl mt-4"><h1 class="font-semibold leading-tight sm:text-3xl text-4xl text-balance text-slate-900">Ethics Researcher / Philosophy nerd</h1><p class="text-xl mt-4 text-slate-600">Research new way to make shrimps happy</p><div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mt-4 text-slate-500 text-sm"><span class="items-center inline-flex gap-2"><span class="rounded-full bg-emerald-500 h-2 w-2"></span> Paris, France / Remote EU </span><span>Posted Nov 10, 2025</span> <span>Full-time</span> <span>Research Ethics Departement</span></div><div class="flex flex-wrap mt-4 font-semibold gap-3 text-xs tracking-wide uppercase"><span class="rounded-full border px-3 py-1 bg-slate-50 border-slate-200 text-slate-700">ethics</span><span class="rounded-full border px-3 py-1 bg-slate-50 border-slate-200 text-slate-700">governance</span><span class="rounded-full border px-3 py-1 bg-slate-50 border-slate-200 text-slate-700">alignment</span> <span class="rounded-full border px-3 py-1 bg-emerald-100 border-emerald-200 text-emerald-700">Remote-friendly</span></div></header></section><section class="mx-auto relative px-4 max-w-4xl z-10 pb-16"><div class="border bg-white border-gray-200 px-6 py-10 rounded-[32px] shadow-xl"><main class="max-w-none prose"><p>Unsuspicious Industries operates at the edge of defensible autonomy, and we need an Ethics Researcher who can translate values into enforceable mechanisms. You will join a hybrid team of philosophers, policy wonks, and systems engineers to ensure our novel deployments remain accountable to society.</p><h3 id="responsibilities">Responsibilities</h3><ul><li>Develop evaluative frameworks for new experiments, deployments, and datasets.</li><li>You convert ethical judgements into typing rules</li><li>Check if we can at all time will that our logical frameworks should become a universal law.</li><li>Track AI developpement, study existentil risk and defend our line on LessWrong in the comment section of Yudkowsky’s posts.</li></ul><h3 id="what-helps">What helps</h3><ul><li>4+ years in applied ethics, safety research, or adjacent risk roles, but a big hatred for the Ai safety folks.</li><li>Working knowledge of technical ML systems and their failure modes.</li><li>Published research, or at least twitter threads with more than 50 likes.</li><li>Knowing around 10 words in at least 5 other language besides English is a plus.</li></ul><p>To apply, send a short note describing what is good, and why.</p></main><div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mt-10"><a class="btn-primary" href="mailto:jobs@unsuspicious.org?subject=Ethics%20Researcher" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Apply for this role</a> <a class="btn-secondary" href="/contact">Talk with our people ops</a></div></div></section></main>
